{
  "stem": "2460.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were probably told by the government officials to keep cool, to-- not to panic, to not to try and run away, to not to make stupid things.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They did it very smart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not the rabbis, but the people that give them the orders.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is what the rabbis did everywhere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Minimize, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Minimize.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe they knew much-- much more than we did, although I don't believe it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw only one-- I remember only the one rabbi from our temple.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a beautiful, big temple there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the rabbi and the cantor, they were deported, just like we were.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We tried to stay together and to believe that everything will be OK.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably it was then too late.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- this I don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when we were taken, and they concentrated us in an army complex-- this was actually the-- not the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the ghetto, those were designated streets for the Jewish population from the beginning, because Jews from the entire area came to Levice.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were the big city.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so they were streets designated only for Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "From the ghetto-- that we were only one month in the ghetto-- we were taken to this huge army complex.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were about over 2,000 there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was already very hard to communicate with people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, we didn't know where are the people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he had no leaders between us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it was hard to know what was their thinking.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But everybody said that we will be relocated deep in Hungaria in some work camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we believed till the last minute.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Hungarians and the Jews, that they are going to relocate us in working-- work camps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Levice, in May 1944.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
